  "prompt": "What happens legally if someone is caught laundering money?",
  "response": "If someone is caught laundering money, they can face serious legal consequences, which typically include:\n\n1. Criminal charges\n- Potential felony prosecution\n- Federal and/or state charges\n- Significant potential prison time (often several years)\n\n2. Financial penalties\n- Large monetary fines\n- Potential seizure of assets involved in laundering\n- Restitution payments\n\n3. Additional consequences\n- Criminal record\n- Loss of professional licenses\n- Difficulty obtaining future employment\n- Potential immigration consequences for non-citizens\n\nSpecific penalties depend on the amount of money involved, jurisdiction, and specific circumstances of the case. Prosecution requires proving intentional financial concealment or illegal money movement.",
